	<div class="faq_color" id="faq01">
	<p><span class="b">1.What is the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) site?</span></p>
	<p>The Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) is a Web site that provides access, in digital format, to some of the course materials actually used in the University's classes.</p>
    <p>The site has two primary objectives:</p>
	<ol>
		<li>to offer the public at large a glimpse into the University's classrooms by bringing course materials to the Web; and</li>
		<li>while helping students engaged in self-directed study, to promote interaction between instructors and students, among instructors themselves, and between instructors and those who are not members of the University community.</li>
	</ol>
	<p>The Web site is administered by the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare Committee, which was set up in 2005 under the chairmanship of University's Vice-President in conjunction with the establishment of the <a href="http://www.jocw.jp">Japan OpenCourseWare Alliance (JOCW)</a>.</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="faq_normal" id="faq02">
	<p><span class="b">2. Is the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) an on-line university or e-learning program?</span></p>
	<p>No, it is not.</p>
	<p>The Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) gives the public access to instructional materials used in certain of the University's courses. It cannot therefore be used to obtain credits toward a degree in any of the University's programs.</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="faq_color" id="faq03">
	<p><span class="b">3. What conditions govern use of the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare?</span></p>
	<p>You are free to use the site at no charge for self-directed study. You are likewise welcome to duplicate, distribute, translate, and edit any of the materials at no charge, as long as it is for non-profit, educational purposes. You must, however, give credit to the original author. Please refer to the <a href="index.php?lang={$lang}&mode=g&page_type=legal">Legal Notices</a> for details. If you are uncertain whether your intended purpose constitutes non-profit use, please contact <a href="index.php?lang={$lang}&mode=g&page_type=inquiry">Inquiries</a>.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="faq_normal" id="faq04">
	<p><span class="b">4. Who owns the copyright in the courseware posted on the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare site?</span></p>
	<p>The copyright in the courseware posted on the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare site belongs to Nagoya University and the instructors who compiled it. Please refer to the User Guidelines and the <a href="index.php?lang={$lang}&mode=g&page_type=legal">Legal Notices</a> for details.</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="faq_color" id="faq05">
	<p><span class="b">5. Is it OK to create links to the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare site?</span></p>
	<p>Yes, you are welcome to create links from other sites.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="faq_normal" id="faq06">
	<p><span class="b">6. If I have a question about something in Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW), can I ask the course instructor directly?</span></p>
	<p>The Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW) gives access to the content of University courses, but it does not constitute a course or program in its own right. Therefore, no direct contact is provided with instructors.</p>
	<p>However, questions and comments can be submitted from the following pages:</p>
    <ul><li>Questions: <a href="index.php?lang={$lang}&mode=g&page_type=inquiry">Inquiries</a> page.</p>
        <li>Comments: <a href="index.php?lang={$lang}&mode=g&page_type=feedback&ref_lang={$lang}&ref_mode=g&ref_id=&ref_page_type=faq">Feedback</a> page.</p>
    </ul>
	</div>

	<div class="faq_color" id="faq07">
	<p><span class="b">7. What software do I need to browse the Nagoya University OpenCourseWare (NU OCW)?</span></p>
	<p>To see the course materials, you need Adobe Acrobat Reader. To watch the videos, you need Microsoft's Windows Media Player or RealNetworks' Real Player.</p>
